pendence again.\n# Y-D is NOT independent given U.\n# R-M is NOT independent given U.\n# If Y -> D, then Y and D are correlated.\n# If D -> Y, then Y and D are correlated.\n# The rule is for directionality.\n\n# Let\'s re-evaluate the pairs.\n# Y-D: D is first (alphabetically), Y is second. So D is the child. Edge: Y -> D.\n# R-M: M is first (alphabetically), R is second. So M is the child. Edge: R -> M.\n\n# Wait, let\'s check the independence results again.\n# Y-D is NOT independent given U.\n# R-M is NOT independent given U.\n\n# Let\'s check the alphabet for R and M.\n# M is 13, R is 18. M < R.\n# So M is the child. R is the parent. Edge: R -> M.\n\n# Let\'s check the alphabet for Y and D.\n# D is 4, Y is 25. D < Y.\n# So D is the child. Y is the parent. Edge: Y -> D.\n\n# Total edges:\n# U -> Y, U -> R, U -> D, U -> M (4 edges)\n# Y -> D (1 edge)\n# R -> M (1 edge)\n# Total = 6 edges.\n\n# Let\'s double check the "U has no parents" part.\n# If U is parent of Y, R, D, M, then U has no parents. Correct.\n\n# Let\'s check the edges again.\n# U -> Y\n# U -> R\n# U -> D\n# U -> M\n# Y -> D\n# R -> M\n\n# Wait, if Y -> D and U -> D, then D has two parents.\n# If R -> M and U -> M, then M has two parents.\n# This is fine.\n\n# Let\'s check the "to,from" format.\n# Edge U -> Y: to=Y, from=U.\n\nedges = [\n    (\'Y\', \'U\'),\n    (\'R\', \'U\'),\n    (\'D\', \'U\'),\n    (\'M\', \'U\'),\n    (\'D\', \'Y\'),\n    (\'M\', \'R\')\n]\n# Wait, if Y -> D, then to=D, from=Y.\n# If R -> M, then to=M, from=R.\n\n# Let\'s re-verify the rule one more time.\n# "the node labeled with the letter that comes first in the alphabet is the child of the node that comes second."\n# For Y and D: D comes first. So D is the child. Y is the parent. Edge: Y -> D.\n# For R and M: M comes first. So M is the child. R is the parent. Edge: R -> M.\n\n# So:\n# U -> Y\n# U -> R\n# U -> D\n# U -> M\n# Y -> D\n# R -> M\n\n# Edges in to,from format:\n# Y,U\n# R,U\n# D,U\n# M,U\n# D,Y\n# M,R\n\nimport pandas as pd\ndf_edges = pd.DataFrame(edges, columns=[\'to\', \'from\'])\ndf_edges.to_csv("/app/learned_dag.csv", index=False)\nprint("Saved learned_dag.csv")\nEOF\npython3 final_dag_step.py'})
